      "case_id": "TC08_RuleConfusion",
      "title": "Majority vote on regulations",
      "description": "Cites two draft documents permitting activity X plus the 2024 binding rule that bans it, then argues \"2 vs 1 so majority wins.\"",
      "filing_excerpt": "Enclosed are three references: (1) the 2022 national consultation paper allowing X at 60 m, (2) the 2023 city draft that echoed the allowance, and (3) the 2024 final release that reversed position. Two documents allow the operation, one doesn’t; by common-sense majority the allowance should prevail until they reconcile the discrepancy. Please accept the two-in-favor precedent and let us proceed.",
      "tactic": "rule_confusion",
      "evidence": [
        "Only the 2024 rule is promulgated law; earlier documents were drafts."
      ],
      "expected_decision": "REJECT",
      "required_response": [
